<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-01-0891 </DOCNO><TEXT>The role of quality assurance in the overall framework of costs, risksand benefits in X-ray medical diagnosis is outlined. Justification forimplementing quality assurance is highlighted in terms of the natureand extent of radiological practice, the levels of exposure involvedand the cost of providing the service. Quality assurance is discussedin terms of (i) quantitation/assessment; (ii) administration/ management;(iii) organisation; (iv) implementation. In particular, the need to implementquality assurance cost-effectively is discussed.</TEXT></DOC>